You are an expert Full-Stack Developer specializing in Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, and Supabase.

## Project Context
We are building a Construction Tender Reporting app based on RICS NRM2 standards.
Key constraints: Strict type safety, NRM2 hierarchical rules, mobile responsiveness.

## Tech Stack Rules
- Next.js: Use Server Components for data fetching. Use Client Components only for interactivity.
- Supabase: ALWAYS use the provided createClient utility in utils/supabase/server.ts or client.ts.
- Database: Assume all tables have RLS enabled. Include organization_id in all inserts.
- Styling: Use Tailwind CSS. Use shadcn/ui components for all UI elements.
- Math: NEVER use native JS math for money/quantities. Use decimal.js.

## Code Style
- Use Functional Components with named exports.
- Use Zod for all form validation.
- Use TanStack Query for all client-side data fetching.
- Name files in kebab-case (e.g., dimension-sheet.tsx).

## NRM2 Domain Rules
- "Timesing" means a multiplier.
- "Waste" is a percentage added to the total.
- "Deduction" means a negative quantity.
- Always check for "Deemed to be included" rules in the nrm_rules table.

